what is locking
_______________

locking is a mechanism used by the address to control concurrent acess data.

it ensures that multiple users access the same data simultaneously the database maintains consistency,
integrity,and prevent conflicts.

1. shared lock
______________

def
___
A shared lock allows a transaction to read data.
multiple transactions can hold a shared lock on the same row.
no transactions can modify the row until all shared locks are released.

characters
__________
read only
multiple users can read simultaneously 
blocks updates and deletes.

2. exclusive lock
_________________
def
___ 
An exclusive lock allows a transaction to modify data.
while an exclusive lock exists :
no other transaction can read using a locking read or modify that row.
only the transaction holding the lock can update/delete the data.

characters:
___________

used for insert,update,delete.
only one exclusive lock at a time.
blocks both reads (locking reads) and writes.



3. intent lock
______________
def
___
An intent lock is a table level lock that indicates a transaction intends to place row level
locks.
it helps MySQL quickly determines whether a table level lock conflicts with existing row locks.
users do not usually create intent locks manually. InnoDB manages them automatically.

Real life example
imagine a library :
shared lock -> many students can read the same book at the same time.
exxclusive-> one student borrows the book , so nobody else can read ar borrow it until it is 
returned.
intent lock-> the librarian marks that someone is about to read or borrow books from a shelf , helping coorodinates access without checking every book individuality.
